<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-11-12T22:26:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-11-12T22:26:00-05:00" n="315" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320/11–1252: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-11-12T22:26:00-05:00">November 12, 1952—10:26
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 183. Re Korea. USGADel advised by
                            Commonwealth sources of following account of most recent conversation
                            between Indian Ambassador in Peiping and <persName corresp="#p_CEL1">Chou En-lai</persName>: <persName corresp="#p_CEL1">Chou
                                En-lai</persName> is reported to have said that release of <gloss target="#t_PW1">PW</gloss>s from American control is the important
                            step. <persName corresp="#p_CEL1">Chou</persName> convinced that if all
                                <gloss target="#t_PW1">PW</gloss>s were released under some neutral
                            control they would all “gradually” be repatriated. It assumed this info
                            conveyed to Indian delegation at UN and may account in part for
                                <persName corresp="#p_MVKK1">Menon</persName>’s present instructions
                            and his persistent determination to table some resolution Friday.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_ADG1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>